WEBVTT

00:08.100 --> 00:11.060
Hi there! Welcome to
this video about

00:11.060 --> 00:13.340
protecting your
digital identity.

00:13.820 --> 00:15.720
This video brings
together everything

00:15.720 --> 00:18.860
you have learned so
far. Digital identity

00:18.860 --> 00:20.820
includes your
accounts, passwords

00:20.820 --> 00:24.280
and online data.
Protecting it helps

00:24.280 --> 00:25.680
keep you safe online.

00:30.000 --> 00:32.460
Your digital identity
includes usernames,

00:32.460 --> 00:35.060
profiles, passwords
and data. It also

00:35.060 --> 00:36.940
includes your
messages, photos and

00:36.940 --> 00:39.440
activity history. All
of these are

00:39.440 --> 00:42.060
connected to you
online. That is why

00:42.060 --> 00:44.740
protection is
important. Digital

00:44.740 --> 00:46.480
identity is valuable
because it gives

00:46.480 --> 00:48.760
access to accounts
and information.

00:48.980 --> 00:52.100
Attackers may want to
steal or misuse it.

00:52.300 --> 00:54.380
Protecting identity
prevents others from

00:54.380 --> 00:57.080
pretending to be you.
It also protects your

00:57.080 --> 01:00.000
reputation. There are
several risks to

01:00.000 --> 01:02.560
digital identity.
These include weak

01:02.560 --> 01:05.040
passwords, sharing
information and

01:05.040 --> 01:08.580
unsafe behaviour.
Phishing messages and

01:08.580 --> 01:11.220
fake links are also
risks. Knowing the

01:11.220 --> 01:13.120
risks helps you avoid
them.

01:17.140 --> 01:19.160
Strong passwords are
one of the most

01:19.160 --> 01:21.500
important protections
. They make it harder

01:21.500 --> 01:24.260
for attackers to
access accounts. Each

01:24.260 --> 01:25.760
account should have
its own strong

01:25.760 --> 01:28.540
password. This limits
damage if one account

01:28.540 --> 01:31.940
is attacked. Password
managers help manage

01:31.940 --> 01:34.520
many strong passwords
safely. They reduce

01:34.520 --> 01:36.900
the need to remember
many passwords. They

01:36.900 --> 01:40.580
also prevent password
reuse. Using them

01:40.580 --> 01:43.260
supports good
security habits.

01:43.260 --> 01:45.940
Privacy settings
control who can see

01:45.940 --> 01:47.980
your information.
They help limit how

01:47.980 --> 01:51.240
much data others can
access. Checking

01:51.240 --> 01:53.540
settings regularly is
a good habit.

01:53.540 --> 01:56.120
Settings are powerful
protection tools.

01:56.360 --> 01:58.240
Logging out is
important on shared

01:58.240 --> 02:00.460
devices. It stops
others from opening

02:00.460 --> 02:03.520
your accounts. Using
device locks also

02:03.520 --> 02:06.120
protects identity.
Small actions make a

02:06.120 --> 02:09.140
big difference.
Phishing messages try

02:09.140 --> 02:11.340
to trick people into
giving information.

02:11.340 --> 02:13.400
They may look urgent
or pretend to be

02:13.400 --> 02:16.280
trusted sources.
Stopping and thinking

02:16.280 --> 02:20.080
helps avoid these
tricks. When unsure,

02:20.080 --> 02:23.440
do not click. Sharing
too much information

02:23.440 --> 02:26.460
can put identity at
risk. Think carefully

02:26.460 --> 02:29.560
before posting or
sending details. Ask

02:29.560 --> 02:33.060
yourself who will see
it and why. Careful

02:33.060 --> 02:36.180
sharing protects
privacy. Old and

02:36.180 --> 02:38.740
unused accounts can
still store data.

02:38.740 --> 02:41.340
Deleting them reduces
risk. A clean digital

02:41.340 --> 02:43.800
space is safer.
Regular cleanups are

02:43.800 --> 02:46.820
helpful. Trusted
adults can help when

02:46.820 --> 02:50.140
something feels wrong
. Asking for help is

02:50.140 --> 02:52.560
a smart choice. It
can prevent mistakes

02:52.560 --> 02:54.880
and problems. You do
not have to handle

02:54.880 --> 02:58.120
issues alone.
Protecting digital

02:58.120 --> 03:00.520
identity is not one
big action. It is

03:00.520 --> 03:03.060
made of small daily
habits. Safe choices

03:03.060 --> 03:05.580
over time add up.
Consistency is

03:05.580 --> 03:06.700
important.

03:10.700 --> 03:13.580
Digital identity
needs protection.

03:13.580 --> 03:16.300
Strong passwords,
managers and careful

03:16.300 --> 03:19.540
behaviour help. Smart
habits keep accounts

03:19.540 --> 03:23.440
and data safe. You
have control over

03:23.440 --> 03:28.500
your digital identity
. You now know how to

03:28.500 --> 03:31.500
protect your digital
identity. Use these

03:31.500 --> 03:34.820
skills every day
online. Stay curious,

03:34.820 --> 03:37.780
stay careful and stay
safe. Thank you for watching.